[2] Background
Date: Wed 22 Jun 2011
Source: GIDEON (Global Infectious Disease & Epidemiology Network)
[edited]
http://www.gideononline.com


re: ProMED-mail Streptococcus group A, scarlet fever - China: (HK)
RFI 20110622.1906
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Rates of scarlet fever in Hong Kong had declined considerably since
the 1970s, but have been increasing during the past decade. Only 6
fatal cases were recorded during 1946 to 2006, the last in 1970. As
seen in the following graph, scarlet fever rates in Macau have
paralleled those of Hong Kong. [1-3]
http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Hong-Kong-Scarlet-fever.jpg

References
----------
1. Berger SA: Infectious Diseases of Hong Kong, 2011. 375 pp, 107
graphs, 1229 references. Gideon e-books series.
http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-hong-kong/.
2. Berger SA: Infectious Diseases of Macao, 2011. 311 pp, 60 graphs,
833 references. Gideon e-books series.
http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-macao/.
3. Berger SA: Rheumatic Fever and Scarlet Fever: Global Status, 2011.
96 pp, 130 graphs, 90 references. Gideon e-books series.
http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/rheumatic-fever-and-scarlet-fever-global-status/.

