[The new information concerning the scarlet fever outbreak in Hong
Kong and neighboring regions presented in the news releases above is
that the total number of cases in Macau is 49 so far this year (2011)
and the number of cases in Hong Kong has risen from 419 to 459.
However, we still do not have any further information on the extent of
the outbreak in neighboring China, other than about "9000 cases" had
occurred there (personal communication, Mary Ann Benitez) from
yesterday's ProMED-mail post (Streptococcus, group A, scarlet fever,
fatal - China: (HK) RFI 20110622.1906). Updated information on the
epidemiology of the outbreak in the affected regions and the
characteristics of the strains of _Streptococcus pyogenes_ involved
would be useful and most appreciated.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Hong Kong and neighboring
China and Macau can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/0_xc. -
Mod.ML]
